**
** ABS HSC Part 3 (2013) S19 - Forward bottom panel - submission-agnostic template
** Spliced into model.inp by wire_bcs.py with:
**   - mesh.inp (gmsh -3 out.step)         provides *NODE + *ELEMENT C3D + Eall
**   - meta.json selectors                  populate NLOAD, NFIX_*MIN/MAX NSETs
**
** Units: mm, N, MPa, t (tonne)
**   pressure 0.05 MPa = 50 kPa  (slamming LC1)
**   density  2.7e-9 t/mm^3      = 2700 kg/m^3
**
** Required NSETs (provided via meta.json selectors):
**   NFIX_XMIN   - x = 0   outer face: simply supported edge
**   NFIX_XMAX   - x = 500 outer face: simply supported edge
**   NFIX_YMIN   - y = 0   outer face: simply supported edge
**   NFIX_YMAX   - y = 1200 outer face: simply supported edge
**
** Required element-face pressure surface (built by wire_bcs.py from
** meta.json "pressure_surfaces" -> emits *SURFACE TYPE=ELEMENT):
**   SURF_NLOAD  - wetted (sea-side) face of the plate (z_min plane)
**
** *SOLID SECTION uses ELSET=Eall (auto-built from gmsh's C3D* volume sets).
**
** Single *STATIC step under LC1 slamming pressure 50 kPa.
** R2 (LC1 vM <= 120 MPa) and R4 (LC2 mid-deflection) are evaluated from
** model.frd; LC2/LC3/LC4 are linearly scaled / superposed in check.py.
** R1 (plate scantling), R5 (stiffener Z), R6 (weld fatigue), R7 (mass)
** are closed-form in check.py.
**
** ---- Material: Al 5083-H116 (welded) ---------------------------------
*MATERIAL, NAME=AL5083
*ELASTIC
70000.0, 0.33
*DENSITY
2.7e-9
**
*SOLID SECTION, ELSET=Eall, MATERIAL=AL5083
**
** ---- Boundary: simply support all four panel edges -------------------
** Pin the four outer side faces of the stiffened panel in 3 DOF. Each
** face represents the panel attached to adjacent framing in the real
** hull. Translational restraint on the outer faces produces the ABS
** "simply supported at stiffeners and frames" boundary.
*BOUNDARY
NFIX_XMIN, 1, 3, 0.0
NFIX_XMAX, 1, 3, 0.0
NFIX_YMIN, 1, 3, 0.0
NFIX_YMAX, 1, 3, 0.0
**
** ---- STEP 1 : LC1 slamming uniform 50 kPa on wetted face -------------
** *DLOAD on the element-face surface SURF_NLOAD applies pressure P to
** every (eid, face) pair in the surface. Sign convention: positive P
** pushes inward to the body, so the slamming pressure on the bottom
** (z_min) face produces a +z reaction (hull pushed up), matching
** ABS HSC Part 3 Section 2.3 slamming.
*STEP
*STATIC
1.0, 1.0
*DLOAD
SURF_NLOAD, P, 0.050
*EL PRINT, ELSET=Eall
S
*NODE FILE
U
*EL FILE
S
*END STEP
